Ticket ID: PC-MAINT-2025-09-SYSINT-01
Title: Comprehensive System Integrity Repair, Windows Update Recovery, and Preventive OS Maintenance
Classification: Preventive Security Maintenance / System Integrity Validation
Execution Period: September 2025
Status: Completed Successfully

Executive Summary
This procedure was executed to restore full system integrity, repair Windows Update functionality, remove corrupted components, eliminate malware persistence vectors, and establish a clean, secure, and verified baseline. All steps were repeated until scans and repair tools returned no integrity violations.
Objectives
	• Restore Windows system integrity and clean baseline
	• Repair Windows Update functionality
	• Remove corrupted system components and residual files
	• Verify disk integrity, component store health, and update mechanisms

Core System Integrity & Repair Procedure
Step 1 — Disk Cleanup
	• Launched Disk Cleanup → removed temp files, Windows Update cache, delivery optimization files, unnecessary system files
Step 2 — System File Integrity Check
	• Command: sfc /scannow → scanned all protected Windows files, replaced corrupted files
	• Repeated until no integrity violations
Step 3 — Full Disk Integrity Check
	• Command: chkdsk /r /f → repaired filesystem, detected bad sectors, recovered data
	• Restart required to complete
Step 4 — DISM Component Store Repair & Cleanup
	• Commands executed:
DISM /Online /Cleanup-Image /CheckHealth
DISM /Online /Cleanup-Image /ScanHealth
DISM /Online /Cleanup-Image /RestoreHealth
DISM /Online /Cleanup-Image /AnalyzeComponentStore
DISM /Online /Cleanup-Image /StartComponentCleanup
DISM /Online /Cleanup-Image /StartComponentCleanup /ResetBase
DISM /Online /Cleanup-Image /SPSuperseded
DISM /Cleanup-Mountpoints
sfc /scannow
	• Actions: verified component store, repaired components, removed obsolete files, repeated until clean
Step 5 — TrustedInstaller Service Repair (If Required)
	• Fixed: Windows Resource Protection could not start repair service
	• Commands:
sc config trustedinstaller start=auto
net start trustedinstaller
sfc /scannow
Step 6 — Windows Update System Reset
	• Services stopped: wuauserv, cryptSvc, bits, msiserver
	• Update cache cleared: C:\Windows\SoftwareDistribution, C:\Windows\System32\catroot2
	• Network reset:
ipconfig /renew
ipconfig /renew6
ipconfig /release
ipconfig /release6
ipconfig /flushdns
netsh winsock reset
	• Cleanup and reset Windows Update Catalog:
net stop bits
net stop msiserver
net stop wuauserv
net stop cryptsvc
Delete C:\Windows\SoftwareDistribution
Delete C:\Windows\System32\Catroot2
• Windows Update Troubleshooter executed
Step 7 — Windows Update Recovery via In-Place Upgrade
	• Process: Media Creation Tool → latest ISO → setup.exe → “Keep personal files and apps”
	• Rebuilt core components while preserving data
Step 8 — Manual Windows Update Installation
	• Updates downloaded from Microsoft Update Catalog and installed to bypass automated failures
Step 9 — Maintenance Software Toolchain
	• Tools: Advanced SystemCare Ultimate, Ashampoo WinOptimizer 25, Black Bird Cleaner, Kerish PC Doctor, Privazer, Wise Care 365, IObit Uninstaller, Snappy Driver Installer, DDU, DriverStore Explorer, Paragon Partition Manager, Sysinternals Autoruns, Sysinternals Process Explorer
	• Actions: system cleanup, driver/software management, inspection, orphaned registry removal, unauthorized persistence elimination
Step 10 — Driver Update & System Stabilization
	• System Restore Point created before updates
	• Drivers updated incrementally with reboots
	• Stability tested → new Restore Point created after stable configuration
	• Temporary driver utilities removed
Step 11 — Network Stack & Connectivity Maintenance
	• Commands: ipconfig /flushdns, netsh winsock reset, netsh int ip reset
	• DNS settings verified and secured
Step 12 — Network Monitoring & Intrusion Detection
	• Tools: Wireshark, netstat -ano, Autoruns, Process Explorer
	• Functions: packet capture, outbound connection detection, traffic inspection, persistence verification
Step 13 — SSD Configuration & Integrity Verification
	• Actions: verified SSD health, partition integrity, extended C partition via Paragon Partition Manager
Step 14 — GPU & System Performance Maintenance
	• NVIDIA cache cleared: C:\ProgramData\NVIDIA Corporation\NV_Cache
	• Power plans restored to defaults: powercfg -restoredefaultschemes
Step 15 — Power Management & Stability Optimization
	• Advanced power settings configured for thermal stability, reduced throttling, and improved reliability
Step 16 — Firmware & Thermal Control
	• FanControl software used to verify fan and thermal behavior
Step 17 — Preventive Maintenance Policy
	• Frequency: 2–3 times/year
	• Includes: restore point creation, driver verification, integrity scans, network monitoring, software cleanup, security validation

Final Outcome
	• Windows component store repaired
	• Windows Update restored
	• Disk and system integrity verified
	• No malware persistence detected
	• Network stack integrity validated
	• System returned to stable, secure baseline
	• All tools returned clean results
